@sodacan , i know this is a strange one.
this is not an issue related to applink protection on android(https://developer.android.com/training/app-links/verify-site-associations#request-verify), this protection is made for avoiding malicious apps to run intent on android > 6.0 on link of other victim website. It's not a deeplink hijacking issue.
Here the protection above is totally bypassable because there is a redirection to another scheme(not http or https) and a malicious app is allowed to handle the protocol and steal the access token in the URI without any authentication.
here a video showing the impact:

{F1282961}

as you can see if you are authenticated and you run the malicious app(evil.apk) above and click the redirect link https://streamlabs.com/global/identity?popup=1&r=test://streamlabs.com the evil app handle the URI scheme and steal the access token.

@sodacan, i hope you are well, there is anything i can do to help you?

NOTE: this bug work in every mobile systems(android and iOS), this attack can be done also in desktop OS but is more common in mobile systems.

thanks @f_m

